<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2 class=news>
<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_general.gif' alt='General News' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top><a href=http://www.planetunreal.com/wod/ target=_blank class=colourise>WoD</a> has posted a nice <a href=http://www.planetunreal.com/wod/reviews/tacops20.html target=_blank class=colourise>review</a> of Tactical Ops Beta 2.0, a realism mod for UT. Here is an excerpt:<br><br><span class=quote>In summary, TacOps is a nice dive into realism but for those players that own Counterstrike, don\'t bother, TacOps is basically a copy of it. For those of you that don\'t have Counterstrike go right ahead and download the whopping 110MB file. I just want to stress the similarities between Counterstrike and TacOps are...incredible.</span><br><br>From that, you wouldn\'t think they liked it but they gave it 97% :)<br><br>Also <a href=http://www.planetunreal.com/modsquad/ target=_blank class=colourise>ModSquad</a>  have a <a href=http://www.planetunreal.com/modsquad/reviews/to2.htm target=_blank class=colourise>review</a> too. The review is very detailed and a good introduction to Tactical Ops. They really liked it. Here is a quote:<br><br><span class=quote>With such an extensive update, there is no wrong doing with Tactical Ops beta 2. New weapons, new net code, new everything basically. It certainly isn\'t the most original concept since there are a ton of realism mods for UT, but it stands out with the amount of content and with the way it presents the content. It\'s semi-realism approach can be compared with Counter-Strike for Half-Life, and so if you liked the mod for Half-Life, I\'m pretty certain that TO beta 2 will fulfill your needs. Of course, it\'s all about a matter of taste, but if To beta 2 sounds like your idea of fun fragging, get downloading if you havne\'t already.</span></td></tr></table>
</td>
