<tr>
<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2 class=news>
<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_general.gif' alt='General News' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top>I recently <a href=http://www.actionnation.com/interview.php?section=10&index=328 class=colourise target=_blank>interviewed</a> Cynic and Psycho, who are the developers of <A href=http://www.planetquake.com/annihilation target=_blank class=colourise>Annihilation</a>, which is a new mod for Quake 3 Arena.  The mod changes the game from its original gothic deathmatch style gameplay to a World War 2 setting. It features a unique class and rank system that makes players dependable of each other. Annihilation is set over a variety of realistic environments in which players have access to realistic weapons, drivable vehicles and a number of gameplay modes, including "Destroy Target" and "Rescue Albert". The interview covers the history of the mod, what will be included in future versions of the mod and what the mod is about. Beta 1.1 has been out for some time and is worth checking out. On the BW FTP, you can find Beta 1 <a href=ftp://ftp.barrysworld.com/pub/games/quake3/mods/annihilation/official_patches/an_beta1.exe class=colourise target=_blank>here</a> and the Beta 1.1 update <a href=ftp://ftp.barrysworld.com/pub/games/quake3/mods/annihilation/official_patches/an_update1.exe class=colourise target=_blank>here</a>. Check it out <a href=http://www.actionnation.com/interview.php?section=10&index=328 class=colourise target=_blank>here</a>.</td></tr></table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
