<tr>
<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2 class=news>
<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_general.gif' alt='General News' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top>I recently <a href=http://www.actionnation.com/interview.php?section=10&index=324 class=colourise>interviewed</a> Democritus and Defcon-X from team mirage, who are the developers of <a href=http://www.planetquake.com/nsq3/ class=colourise target=_blank>Navy Seals : Covert Operations</a>, which is a new mod for Quake 3 Arena. The mod will be a realistic warfare simulator in which players will fight as either Seals or Tangos. It could be described as a mix between Counter-Strike and Rainbow Six but the developers feel that you will need to play the mod in order to understand the unique aspects of its gameplay. It should feature around 20 different weapons and a large number of maps set over a variety of settings, including urban and desert. There is no release date yet but the <a href=http://www.actionnation.com/interview.php?section=10&index=324 class=colourise>interview</a> contains a lot of information on the mod. Check it out <a href=http://www.actionnation.com/interview.php?section=10&index=324 class=colourise>here</a>.</td></tr></table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
