<td bgcolor="#CECECE" class="btext" width="100%"><b>Military Forces Q3</b> - <span class=bsmall>posted by  <a class='nNewsMailLink' href='mailto:deathwatch@barrysworld.com'>Deathwatch</a> on Tue 31 July 2001 14:39:36 | <a href="comments.php?section=1&index=320" class=blink>Comments (0)</a></span></td>
<td bgcolor="#CECECE" width=17><img src="images/item_icon.gif" width="17" height="17" alt="" border="0"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2 class=news>
<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_general.gif' alt='General News' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top><a href="http://www.planetquake.com/mfq3" class=colourise>Military Forces</a>, an Quake 3 Arena mod, is different from most others, in the way that it allows you to fly planes and drive around with tanks, like Air Quake 2. It's no suprise that the team consists of members from both Air Quake and Air Quake 2.<br><br>MFQ3 has released an early alpha today, which features the following things:<br><br><span class=quote>Movement -<br> No longer are you constrained to the 2 feet that q3a provides you with. You can take to the skies in a jet or roll over the dunes in a tank. Eventualy one will also be able to hover over the battle field in a helo, run through the trenches as an infantry man, or perhaps even the chance to float across a river in a boat while trying to avoid air raids from the enemy.<br><br>Gamesets -<br> These are sub-mods within the TC that allow for a more diversified look into the military world. So far there are only 2 included; Modern, featuring 4 jets and 2 grond vehicals, and WorldWar2, showcasing 2 WW2 era dog fighters as a sneak preview of whats to come.<br><br>Vehicals - <br> Modern) <br>  Jets: F-5, F-15, F-16, JAS-39<br>  Ground Vehicals: M1, BRDM2<br> WW2)<br>  Planes: Spitfire, Mustang<br><br>Weapons -<br> Machineguns, rocketpods, and free falling iron bombs for the jets, ballistic 125 mm gun on the M1 and machine guns on both tanks as well as an impressive aray of cannons on the ww2 dogfighters. As the versions progress, more advanced weapons such as guided missiles/bombs, mines, and anti aircraft ammunitions will be added.<br><br>New HUD(Heads Up Display) -<br> You now have all the information required to help you destroy the enemy. Everything from fuel and weapons loadout to throttle setings and a handy RADAR to know where the enemy is, but be careful, as it will give away your position as well. The crosshair will give you pin-point acuracy when firing on the other plane in that intense dogfight, and the new UI(User Interface) will let you choose your vehical and jump into the fray before you can say supercalafragelisticexpialedocious.<br> <br>Map Entities -<br> Runways and destroyable buildings now grace the terrain with control towres and other features soon to come.</span><br><br>Sounds interesting? Head over to <a href="http://www.planetquake.com/mfq3" class=colourise>their site</a> for more information or download the early alpha version <a href="http://www.planetquake.com/dl/dl.asp?mfq3/mfq3_full_alpha037.zip" class=colourise>here</a>.</td></tr></table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
