<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2 class=news>
<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_general.gif' alt='General News' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top><a href="http://www.idsoftware.com" class=colourise>id Software</a> released a new patch of Quake 3 Arena yesterday, v1.29g. <br><br>This version does the following:<br><span class=quote>- Players joining (and apparently leaving) the game cause everyone to hitch<br>- fs_handleforfile: none free ERROR<br>- No sound in NT 4.0 at all with 1.29f PR<br>- There is a shader bug in Pro-q3dm6<br>- made /startOrbit cheatprotected<br>- Rcon issues now resolved.<br>- fs_basegame isn't published to clients<br>- fixedlegs command in the animation config is apparently not working<br>- + and - cvars fixed<br>- After last level of tier game doesn't stay on trophy screen, instead it takes you directly to next tier screen<br>- developer cheats like R_Showtris have been disabled in the PR (they were never disabled, the user simply needs to run the game with "+set developer 1" minus quotes, at the command line.</span><br><br>This patch can be downloaded from all the major sites and ofcourse from <a href="ftp://ftp.barrysworld.com/pub/games/quake3/official_patches/win32/q3pointrelease_129g_beta.exe" class=bwlink>BarrysWorld FTP</a>.<br><br>Robert Duffy also reports that there might be some glitches with the installer:<br><br><span class=quote>"I have seen a few reports of the full Win32 installer not properly installing the latest PAK3 files. Looking into this now, if there is an there is an issue, I'll get more info/fixes up tomorrow ( Saturday )."</span></td></tr></table>
