<td bgcolor="#CECECE" class="btext" width="100%"><b>True Combat Stuff</b> - <span class=bsmall>posted by  <a class='nNewsMailLink' href='mailto:deathwatch@barrysworld.com'>Deathwatch</a> on Wed 25 July 2001 19:00:27 | <a href="comments.php?section=1&index=309" class=blink>Comments (0)</a></span></td>
<td bgcolor="#CECECE" width=17><img src="images/item_icon.gif" width="17" height="17" alt="" border="0"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2 class=news>
<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_general.gif' alt='General News' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top>TeamTerminator, the developers of <a href="" class=colourise>True Combat</a>, a realistic Quake 3 Arena mod, have announced that they are going to release their beta 0.45 on 27/7/2001:<br><span class=quote>"TrueCombat beta045 with its numerous new features such as free climbing, precise aim system, realistic physics and ballistics, light glare effect on scopes, holstering system, is nothing short of revolutonary and it will make heads turn. Everything from the maps to the weapon models was made to ensure that the mod would be very cohese, so we ended up with a very orginal and dark mod."</span><br><br>Also, <a href="http://www.q3center.com" class=colourise>Q3Center</a> has conducted <a href="http://www.q3center.com/features/features.phtml?id=88842&language=en" class=colourise>an interview</a> with them, which covers the origins of the mod and what it'll contain and it's future.</td></tr></table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
