<td bgcolor="#CECECE" class="btext" width="100%"><b>Epic Games FAQ</b> - <span class=bsmall>posted by  <a class='nNewsMailLink' href='mailto:deathwatch@barrysworld.com'>Deathwatch</a> on Wed 25 July 2001 18:41:01 | <a href="comments.php?section=1&index=307" class=blink>Comments (0)</a></span></td>
<td bgcolor="#CECECE" width=17><img src="images/item_icon.gif" width="17" height="17" alt="" border="0"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2 class=news>
<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_general.gif' alt='General News' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top><a href="http://www.epicgames.com" class=colourise>Epic Games</a> have posted a <a href="http://www.epicgames.com/faq.html" class=colourise>FAQ</a>. This small FAQ doesn't only cover their games, such as Unreal Tournament, but also covers other things like what to do if you want to make a movie/book/comic/whatever based on any of their games:<br><br><span class=quote>"We would consider inquiries from major established studios, publishers, merchandisers or production companies who are willing to pay up-front licensing fees or attach major stars / musicians / authors / artists to the project but unfortunately we can't accommodate requests from individuals."</span></td></tr></table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
