<td bgcolor="#CECECE" class="btext" width="100%"><b>Firearms News</b> - <span class=bsmall>posted by  <a class='nNewsMailLink' href='mailto:ice.m@btinternet.com'>ICE.M</a> on Sat 21 July 2001 18:08:56 | <a href="comments.php?section=1&index=301" class=blink>Comments (0)</a></span></td>
<td bgcolor="#CECECE" width=17><img src="images/item_icon.gif" width="17" height="17" alt="" border="0"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2 class=news>
<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_general.gif' alt='General News' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top>The <a href=http://www.firearmsmod.com/ class=colourise target=_blank>Firearms</a> site has been updated with lots of news on the mod. They talk about the new player models, new maps, bug fixes and gameplay changes that will be in <a href=http://www.firearmsmod.com/ class=colourise target=_blank>Firearms</a>  2.6. The update includes a number of screenshots and renders, showing player models, maps and weapons. Check it out <a href=http://www.firearmsmod.com/ class=colourise target=_blank>here</a>. In related news, <a href=http://www.fa-nation.net/ class=colourise target=_blank>FA-Nation</a>  have a <a href=http://www.fa-nation.net/template.php?content=preview2.fa-n class=colourise target=_blank>preview</a> of <a href=http://www.firearmsmod.com/ class=colourise target=_blank>Firearms</a> 2.6.  They talk about the models, the maps and other features. It includes renders of all weapons and all of the new maps. It is well worth a look if you like playing <a href=http://www.firearmsmod.com/ class=colourise target=_blank>Firearms</a>. Check it out <a href=http://www.fa-nation.net/template.php?content=preview2.fa-n class=colourise target=_blank>here</a>.</td></tr></table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
